    "children": [
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Ancient China is one of the most flavourful settings one can choose to have their game set in: millennia of culture and history, rich mythology and endless possibilities. In ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Detective Di: The Silk Rose Murders",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", Nupixo Games takes upon themselves the task of showing the player a clever story full of twists and turns set in ancient China, following the young magistrate Di Renjie. Based on real historical characters and events, and then heavily stylized into an engaging point-and-click puzzle game, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Detective Di: The Silk Rose Murders",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " tries to stand tall among the celebrated genre, and it might just have what it takes.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wySeGb--4vE",
        "html": "<iframe width=\"200\" height=\"113\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wySeGb--4vE?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>",
        "metadata": {
          "title": "Detective Di: The Silk Rose Murders | Launch Trailer | Nintendo Switch | Xbox One / Series S&X",
          "author_name": "RedDeerGames",
          "author_url": "https://www.youtube.com/c/RedDeerGames",
          "height": 113,
          "width": 200,
          "version": "1.0",
          "provider_name": "YouTube",
          "provider_url": "https://www.youtube.com/",
          "thumbnail_height": 360,
          "thumbnail_width": 480,
          "thumbnail_url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wySeGb--4vE/hqdefault.jpg"
        },
        "embedType": "video"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Good - Aren’t you a clever one?",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "There is one aspect that stands atop every other in ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Detective Di",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", and that is the story. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Detective Di",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " weaves its story patiently, taking the time to introduce and establish each character, including our main protagonist — the young magistrate Di Renjie. The story keeps the engagement high, starting off slow and expanding quickly into something more. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Detective Di",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is a very clever game in no small part due to the narrative that feels like an excellent political mystery series that is allowed to breathe and develop organically. The player is free to engage with the characters as much as possible, learn about them in many ways and through these characters, see the world brought to life.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "html",
        "html": "<a href=\"https://powera.pxf.io/c/3324894/1309898/15385\" target=\"_top\" id=\"1309898\"><img src=\"//a.impactradius-go.com/display-ad/15385-1309898\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"728\" height=\"90\"/></a><img height=\"0\" width=\"0\" src=\"https://imp.pxf.io/i/3324894/1309898/15385\" style=\"position:absolute;visibility:hidden;\" border=\"0\" />"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The second strongest point of the game is, of course, the puzzles. Almost all of them are cleverly made with strong ties to the world of the game, requiring a lot of critical thought. Clever players will be able to see a few steps ahead and realise where the puzzle is going beforehand, experiencing a real sense of satisfaction in the process by making their own theories alongside Detective Di. Of course, not all of them are necessarily story related — sometimes it’s just the kind of day where the detective has to figure out how to get a cat down from the ceiling. The puzzles all serve a purpose, be it progressing the story, adding to worldbuilding and levity or expanding characterisation. They are all of varied purposes and design and certainly more than one example will be memorable for any player.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 1,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "TL;DR",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Excellent story and characters",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "listitem",
